Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>+10% <span class=3DSpellE>sublight</span> sp=
eed </p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l2 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>+10% shield and shield recharge </p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l2 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>+10% weapon range and weapon travel speed </=
p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l2 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>+10% weapon damage (every other weapon under=
 10
damage will receive +1 damaged instead) </p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l=
2 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>+25% targeting, countermeasures, -20% static
energy usage, +10% fuel capacity</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>In addition, crews above &#8220;green&#8221; have a li=
mited
ability to repair damaged components on their ship.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Also, ships that have a repair mission and manage to
self-repair (through any means) will have their repair mission cancelled.</=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Fighter Aces<=
/b>: As
with crews, fighters can gain experience as well. When a pilot obtains his
first experience perk he will get a custom name.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Exploration s=
hip and
construction ship size</b>: These two ships max size is now the same as an
empire&#8217;s military ship max size. Previously they we not modified by
either military or civilian empire size factor.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Bacon Civilian
Shipyards</b>: The game now uses the pirate ship building interface <span
class=3DGramE>so</span> you can build all ship classes now. Need 50 freight=
ers?
Don&#8217;t wait for the private sector. Build them yourself. Note that the=
se
ships will be state ships and the state will pay their maintenance costs.</=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Armed Civilia=
n Ships</b>:
Civilian ships can now have up to 10 weapons.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Order Passeng=
er Ships</b>:
If you have a passenger ship selected and press Ctrl-W the game will perfor=
m a
passenger transport mission from SOURCE to DESTINATION as defined in
passengers.txt. Be sure to only do this for a passenger ship that doesn&#82=
17;t
already have passengers otherwise the existing passengers may disappear into
limbo. Not a lot of error checking here so make sure you spell the planet n=
ame
exactly correct (copy past from within the game is best). Note: you can keep
the passengers.txt file open. Just save it after updating it and the new
setting will take effect.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>If you hold down SHIFT while assigning a mission to a =
state
passenger ship the mission will repeat until you clear it with the ship fin=
der
(!clear).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Bacon Input (=
Ship
Finder)</b>: Press control-E to bring up a search box. Type the name of any=
 one
of your ships or planets and the first match will become the selected objec=
t.
Good for when you have 500+ ships and know the name but don&#8217;t feel li=
ke
searching through the <span class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> (even sorted the=
 <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> can still be a chore).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Please note, The <span class=3DSpellE>ShipFinder</span=
> has
now been renamed &#8220;Bacon Input&#8221; because it now does so much more.
All special commands (those starting <span class=3DGramE>with !</span> or #=
) are
input through this box.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Fleet Command=
s</b>:
Using the ship finder, with a fleet selected you can do the following:</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:=
l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>#combine fleet1+fleet2 &#8211; this will com=
bine
the two into the first fleet and eliminate the second fleet.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>#disband <span class=3DSpellE>fleetName</spa=
n>
&#8211; this will disband the named fleet and set each ship to auto control=
led.</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>#join <span class=3DSpellE>fleetName</span>
&#8211; currently selected ships (not a fleet) will join the named fleet.</=
p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l=
1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>#add <span class=3DSpellE>shipDesign</span>=
=3DNumber
&#8211; this will find &#8216;number&#8217; of ships of design &#8216;<span
class=3DSpellE>shipdesign</span>&#8217; and add them to the currently selec=
ted
fleet. Ships already in another fleet, damaged ships, and ships low on fuel
will be excluded from the command.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Assign Cargo =
Mission</b>:
Select a freighter and press Alt-3 to order it to move resources from SOURC=
E to
DESTINATION. SOURCE is set by selecting the desired source and pressing Alt=
-1.
DESTINATION is set with Alt-2. Source and destination remain set until you
change it or reload a saved game so you can order several freighters on the
same route quickly. Freighters will pick up all resources that the source h=
as
in large quantity. If multiple resources are present in the same amount then
the freighter will split its cargo hold evenly between them.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>If you hold down SHIFT while assigning a mission to a =
state
freighter the mission will repeat until you clear it with the ship finder
(!clear).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>If the mission target is a construction ship the freig=
hter
will try to fill up the constructor&#8217;s holds evenly with each type of
strategic resource.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>To force a manual cargo mission to carry just the reso=
urces
you want you can use <span class=3DGramE>the !</span>cargos command as foll=
ows:</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!cargos, [carg=
o name],
[cargo2 name], <span class=3DSpellE>etc</span><o:p></o:p></i></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Example<span class=3DGramE>: <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font=
-style:
normal'>!</i></span><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>cargos, Caslon,=
 <span
class=3DSpellE>Dilithium</span> Crystal</i> (Note, you must put a comma bet=
ween
each term including the word cargos and the first assigned cargo.)</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>To clear the list just <span class=3DGramE>enter <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-=
style:
normal'>cargos</i> with nothing after it.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Assign Mining
Mission:</b><span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Select a planet =
you
wish to mine and press <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Alt-M</i>. T=
he
closest mining ship without a mission will move there to mine it. It will
deliver the cargo to the closes space station. If you press <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Alt-Shift-A</i> and you have a specific
destination set (with <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Alt-2</i>) th=
en it
will deliver to that destination instead. As always you can order a ship to=
 not
unload with <span class=3DGramE>the <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'=
>!</i></span><span
class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>nodump</i></span> co=
mmand.
After giving this order the ordered ship will be selected.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>More Ship Ima=
ges</b>:
Each family of ships can have up to four more images for <span class=3DGram=
E>each</span>
class of ship. So you can have &#8220;destroyer&#8221;, &#8220;destroyer1<s=
pan
class=3DGramE>&#8221;, &#8230;</span> &#8220;destroyer4&#8221;.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Full Freighte=
rs</b>:
Freighters will always try to max out their load if their destination is a =
base
or planet. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Fighter Fun</=
b>:
Fighters/Bombers can have longer range. In addition, fighters from bases wi=
ll
always have 1.4 times the range of other fighters. Other fighter options
included limited ammo, cost to build, build time, and extra damage against =
bombers.
See BaconSettings.txt for details.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:=
normal'>HyperFun</b></span>:
<span class=3DSpellE>Hyperjump</span> settings can be changed from the
BaconSettings.txt file. See file comments for details.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Better Interf=
ace</b>:
Diplomacy screen has higher money amounts for deals larger than 10,000 cred=
its.
Font and background <span class=3DSpellE>colors</span> (drop shadow) change=
d on
some screens for better readability.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
</span>This is set with Shadow=3Dfalse in the <span class=3DSpellE>config</=
span>
file.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>When designing a ship, selecting an existing component=
 will
auto select the same component on the left-hand list unless the selected
component is <span class=3DGramE>obsolete.</span> This way you can easily a=
dd
more of an existing component.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Items on the diplomacy screen are now ordered
alphabetically. Extra cash options above 10,000 have been added if you have=
 the
cash available.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Shiplist</span> screen and fleet =
display
in the info panel now have <span class=3DSpellE>color</span> indicators to
differentiate damage types. Yellow ships have only <span class=3DSpellE>arm=
or</span>
damaged. Aqua ships have lost their <span class=3DSpellE>hyperdrive</span>.=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Order multipl=
e troops</b>:
With the desired planet select on the colonies screen, bring up the ship fi=
nder
and type &#8220;<span class=3DGramE>!troops</span> X&#8221; to order up X n=
umber
of troops. This will save a lot of clicking if you build a lot of troops.</=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Ship Cycler</=
b>: <span
class=3DGramE>Alt ;</span> and Alt &#8217; to cycle backward/forward throug=
h all
of your ships with the same <span class=3DSpellE>subrole</span> as the curr=
ently
selected ship. If you have your view locked (&#8216;L&#8217; key) the view =
will
change with each selection. (If Alt doesn&#8217;t work try Ctrl.)</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Cargo Mission=
 Viewer</b>:
With a freighter with a cargo mission selected, press <span class=3DSpellE>=
<i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>ctrl+enter</i></span> to see its missi=
on
cargo order and its current cargo.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Damage Viewer=
</b>:
View a list of damaged components with control-R.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Science Ships=
</b>:
Automated exploration ships with labs will pursue research projects
independently. Each science ship will pick one research project for each ty=
pe
of lab it has (Energy, high-tech, weapons). Each month it will contribute
research points toward that project until it if learned. The amount if set =
in
the settings file. After the first month you can use the new Alt + Ctrl + r=
ight
click menu to set the specific research project for the science ship.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Bomber Bays</=
b>:
Fighter bays and bomber bays can now be separate, allowing you to choose how
many of each type your carriers carry. This requires the <span class=3DSpel=
lE>BaconWorld</span>
components.txt, research.txt and fighters.txt files. AI ships will keep the
50/50 split between fighters and bombers. The settings file allows you to
specific a specific string that the game will look for in each fighter bay
component to determine if that bay will produce fighters, bombers or an even
split.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Stars and Gal=
axy Size</b>:
Number of stars is no longer limited by galaxy size. Previously a 4x4 galaxy
had a limit of 400 stars. The star limit increased by one notch on the slid=
er
for each increase in the galaxy size. This limit has been removed. Also, a =
new
size &#8220;Bacon Big&#8221; has been added with 2000 stars.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Additionally, the lowest star setting value can be
overwritten with the <span class=3DSpellE>lowStarCount</span> value in the
settings file. Note that in order for this value to be used on a new game y=
ou
have to start or load a game to get the settings to initialize and then go =
to
the main screen and start your actual game.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Custom Start =
Screen</b>:
If your mod contains a file called &#8220;customBackgroundImage.jpg&#8221; =
in
the \Customization\[mod name]\images folder, it will use that one instead of
the regular DWU start screen. Please note that the game title &#8220;Distant
Worlds Universe&#8221; is actually on the start screen so if you replace it
with a custom start screen you should probably include &#8220;Distant Worlds
Universe&#8221; somewhere on the new screen for legal reasons.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Integration w=
ith
Bacon Stats Viewer</b>: The game will dump two xml files
&#8220;SaveStatsEmpires.xml&#8221; and &#8220;SaveStatsPirates.xml&#8221; t=
hat
will track game stats such as income, military strength, population, etc. T=
hese
files can be viewed in the Bacon stats viewer. The viewer can be left open =
and
just click the &#8216;refresh&#8217; button to get an update. Note that the=
se
two files have to be deleted when starting a new game or else you will still
have the old game stats and it will look ugly. The interval for dumping dat=
a is
configurable in the settings file. Default is 90 days.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Asteroid Colo=
nies</b>:
Colony ships can now create asteroid colonies. The procedure is slightly
different from a regular colonize mission. Order your colony ship to the
asteroid and then use the new <span class=3DSpellE>alt+ctrl</span>+ right c=
lick
menu and select the colonize option. This will create a 30,000 person colon=
y on
the asteroid and deduct the amount of credits configured in the settings fi=
le.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Terraforming<=
/b>: The
terraforming facility (#9 in Facilities.txt) now has its second and third
values used to raise a planet&#8217;s habitability rating. Previously they =
were
zero. The second value is the rate of terraforming and the third value is t=
he
limit to which habitability can be raised. Default values are 500 and 80.</=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Hold Position=
</b>:
Using the new Alt + Ctrl + Right Click menu a ship can be told to hold posi=
tion
and will ignore all orders (from player or AI) to do anything else until you
cancel the hold order. This is useful to prevent ships from flying off and
attacking other threats in system, for example.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Trade Everyth=
ing</b>:
If this option is enabled in the settings file all known bases and planets =
will
appear on the diplomacy trade screen. This has been made optional because s=
ome
people have reported the game taking up to 15 minutes to load this screen w=
hen
there are hundreds of bases in the late game.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Also, bases attached to a colony w=
ill
not be tradable even if this option is enabled. It causes too many weird
situations since those bases share their cargo with the colony. Regardless =
of
the setting CTRL-T will add the currently selected base (or ship) to the tr=
ade
screen the next time it is opened. It is cleared after closing the trade
screen.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>!note</b>: Th=
is will
add a reminder note to the currently selected ship. When the ship completes=
 its
mission it will <span class=3DSpellE>popup</span> the message and allow you=
 to
select the ship if desired. Leave a space <span class=3DGramE>between !</sp=
an>note
and your message. To clear a message just <span class=3DGramE>type !</span>=
note
with no message.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>War Weariness=
</b>: In
default Distant Worlds all war weariness is reset to zero when your last war
ends. Instead, it will drop slowly over time.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Weapon Range =
Circles</b><span
class=3DGramE>:<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>!</span><span
class=3DSpellE>rangecircles</span> toggles this on and off. With it on, the
current selected ship will have circles around it showing the range of its
weapons.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Since enemy weapon r=
ange
is displayed in vanilla DW, the range circles work for enemy ships as well.=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Reload Ship T=
emplates</b>
&#8211; Normally ship templates for AI empires are only loaded on game start
(or when a new empire is created). Now you can make changes to the templates
and have the game reload them to take effect in your current game. The comm=
and
for this <span class=3DGramE>is <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</=
i></span><span
class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>loadtemplates</i></s=
pan>. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!<span class=
=3DSpellE>loadtemplates</span>
<span class=3DGramE>true<span style=3D'font-style:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>will</span></span></i> include the
player&#8217;s empire. Otherwise it will only apply to AI empires. To use t=
his
command, go to the <span class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> screen and select t=
he
classes of ships for which you want the Ai to regenerate designs. Then use
ctrl-e and enter the command. Note that it will not obsolete your old desig=
ns
so you might want to do that first manually. <span class=3DSpellE>Alao</spa=
n>, it
will pick new names for your new designs so you may want to rename them
afterward.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>No Independen=
ts</b> <span
class=3DGramE>-<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>A</span> new =
setting
in the Baconsettings.txt file allows you to override the <span class=3DSpel=
lE>loswest</span>
setting of the &#8220;independent life slider bar&#8221; on galaxy creation.
The lowest setting corresponds to a value of 150. You can lower it as low a=
s 1
to get rid of independents. Do not set it to zero as it is used as a diviso=
r in
some places and will crash. You may still see some independents but they are
probably pirates. Also, if you try to load a saved game that used a differe=
nt
value you MAY get a failure to load. This has not been extensively tested a=
nd
should be considered experimental. Like the &#8220;low stars&#8221; setting=
, it
is not initialized until after a game starts so if you want to see the affe=
cts
you must either start or load a game and THEN go back to the main menu and
start your actual game.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Improved mini=
ng cap
with tech increase</b> &#8211; Value 2 (which is zero in vanilla DW) is now
used to override the mining rate cap. In <span class=3DSpellE>unmodded</spa=
n> DW
the mining rate cap is 10 for mining and luxury mining and 40 for gas minin=
g.
You can now change that with tech advanced. See the entries in research.txt=
 for
suggested values. If you leave it as zeros then the default values will be =
used
(10, 10, <span class=3DGramE>40</span>).</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Loans</b> <sp=
an
class=3DGramE>-<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>You</span> ca=
n now
get a loan when you need more cash. !loan [amount] will let you see how the
terms of the loan and, if you agree, you will take out the loan. <span
class=3DGramE>Entering !</span>loan without an amount will show you any
outstanding loans you currently have.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Ransoming Cap=
tured
Spies</b> &#8211; There is now a chance that a captured spy will be put in
prison instead of killed. This is controlled in the <span class=3DSpellE>Ba=
conSettigns</span>
with a value between 0.0 and 1.0 where 1.0 means a captured spy will always=
 be
taken alive and put in prison. Open the prisoner screen with Ctrl-P to view
your prisoners as well as your spies being held on other planets that are
available to ransom back. When a spy is captured you won&#8217;t know right
away if the AI will allow them to be ransomed back. They will make that
decision at some point in the future (usually 45-180 days). Spies may also
defect or escape. The chance of this is configurable in the settings file.<=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Remove Backgr=
ound
Stars</b>: When zoomed out the background stars are displayed using an
image&#8221; images\environment\<span class=3DSpellE>galaxybackdrops</span>=
\galaxy_backdrop.jpg&#8221;.
Replacing this with a solid black image will remove the stars. When zoomed =
in
the stars are drawn programmatically. You can now set the level of zoom whe=
re
the stars will be drawn. Set <span class=3DSpellE>backgroundStarsAtZoomLeve=
l</span>=3D0
in the BaconSettings.txt to remove background stars. <span class=3DSpellE><=
span
class=3DGramE>backgroundStarsAtZoomLevel</span></span><span class=3DGramE>=
=3D</span>300
is the default level.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>New <span
class=3DSpellE>Shiplist</span> options</b>: The <span class=3DSpellE>shipli=
st</span>
screen has extra selection options: damaged ships, low fuel ships, etc. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>In addition, if you have a ship or planet selected the=
 <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> will have a default sort order based on dist=
ance
from the selected object. If you have selected a column header and sorted y=
our <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> then the game will continue to use the sort =
order
you selected. To unsort a <span class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> click the co=
lumn
with the empire flag. If no object is selected the game will use the normal=
 <span
class=3DSpellE>shiplist</span> <span class=3DSpellE>behavior</span>.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Free Traders<=
/b>:
Using the <span class=3DGramE>command <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:norma=
l'>!</i></span><span
class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>freetrader</i></span=
><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> X</i> turns a state-run freighter int=
o an
independent trader with X initial cash (taken as a loan from your state fun=
ds).
To pay off your loan, once you&#8217;ve earned some cash, <span class=3DGra=
mE>use
!</span><span class=3DSpellE>freetrader</span> with a negative value for X.=
 To
retire and return your freighter to general service, <span class=3DGramE>us=
e <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><span class=3DSpellE><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>freetrader</i></span><i style=3D'mso-b=
idi-font-style:
normal'> 0</i>. To trade with a planet or base use the <span class=3DSpellE=
><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>alt+Ctrl+right</i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'> click</i> menu when you are within ra=
nge
300. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Some items on the trade panel are <span class=3DSpellE=
>color</span>
coded. Gold and silver are commodities which are higher priced than usual. =
Try
to sell these. Light green and red are commodities below market value. Try =
to
buy these. <span class=3DGramE>Use <i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>=
!</i></span><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>price</i> to help you find a good plac=
e to
buy or sell. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Free traders pay for their own maintenance, not the st=
ate
unless they are automated and then the state pays the maintenance. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Free traders can also collect resources and even ship
components from ships they defeat in battle. These ship components can be i=
nstalled
at any independent planet or asteroid colony using the alt ctrl right click
menu. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Free traders can <span class=3DSpellE>aslo</span> recr=
uit
officers with the alt ctrl right click menu. The cost is set in the
BaconSettings.txt file. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Note: the free trader price system takes about a year =
to
fully seed in a new game so it is advised to wait a year before making a fr=
ee
trader.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Subjugation T=
ribute</b>:
The percent of income that subjugated empires pay as tribute has been made
modifiable. It is controlled by the setting <span class=3DSpellE>Subjugatio=
nTributePercentage</span>
in the BaconSettings.txt file.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Longer range =
weapons
on bases</b>: You can now configure bases to have a weapon range longer than
ships. The setting that controls this is in the BaconSettings.txt <span
class=3DSpellE>weaponRangeMultiplierForBases</span>. It is a multiple so 2 =
equals
200% normal range. Make bases great again.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Infrastructur=
e:</b>
You can now add infrastructure improvements to a colony with <span class=3D=
GramE>the
<i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><i style=3D'mso-bidi-fo=
nt-style:
normal'>infrastructure</i> command. This will raise the development level of
the colony. Settings are configurable in the BaconSettings.txt file. You can
check how much of an effect you are receiving by selecting the planet and
pressing <span class=3DSpellE>Ctrtl</span>-Enter.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Zoom with mou=
se wheel
when other menus are open:</b> You can now use the mouse wheel to zoom even
when other menus are open. If the menu is focused on a control, such as a <=
span
class=3DSpellE>listbox</span>, that scrolls when using the mouse wheel, you=
 will
have to select something else before zooming. Hold down right mouse button =
to
drag the map.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Ship ETA to W=
aypoint:</b>
Ships now show the estimated time until arrival at their next waypoint in
seconds. This is only for individual ships, not ships in fleets.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Pirate commis=
sion
ships at Independent colonies:</b> Pirates can now commission construction
ships to be built at independent colonies they control. Select the planet a=
nd use
the alt-Ctrl-right click menu.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Repair and re=
fit only
bases: </b>Bases whose name begins with -- will only repair and refit ships=
 but
not initiate new construction. This can help you manage where new ships wil=
l be
built and avoid long delays caused from building at bases low on resources.=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Ship targeting
restrictions:</b> A ship (or fleet) can be given a targeting restriction to
avoid targeting certain types of targets. The command <span class=3DGramE>i=
s <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><span class=3DSpellE><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>notarget</i></span><i style=3D'mso-bid=
i-font-style:
normal'> [type]</i> where type can be any of:</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:=
l0 level1 lfo6'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Bases</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l0 level1 lfo6'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Military</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list=
:l0 level1 lfo6'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Stronger</p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-18.0pt;mso-list:l=
0 level1 lfo6'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]>Faster</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Enter with no parameter to clear the setting. While the
setting can be given to a fleet that just passes the setting to each ship in
the fleet. There is no setting for the fleet so if you add ships to the fle=
et
later you should reissue the setting. You can check a ship&#8217;s setting =
with
<i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Ctrl-Enter</i>.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:=
normal'>PointDefense</b></span><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'> and Missiles:</b> With this option s=
et to
true in the settings file point <span class=3DSpellE>defense</span> and beam
weapons can intercept missiles. The point <span class=3DSpellE>defense</spa=
n>
weapons will fire their animation but the beam weapons won&#8217;t. Instead=
 I
added a small animation to show the missile has been shot down. The
interception isn&#8217;t 100% and there is a myopic zone if you get too clo=
se.
Also there is a bug that sometimes allows missiles to <span class=3DSpellE>=
insta</span>-hit
their target regardless of point <span class=3DSpellE>defense</span>. It&#8=
217;s <span
class=3DSpellE>kinda</span> rare. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Split off a p=
lanet to
from a new Empire:</b> The <span class=3DGramE>command <i style=3D'mso-bidi=
-font-style:
normal'>!</i></span><span class=3DSpellE><i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:no=
rmal'>splitoff</i></span>
can be used to give independence to a planet in your empire that you
don&#8217;t want anymore. The newly formed empire will start with a positive
relationship bonus due to being granted independence. Alternatively, you can
add &#8220;false&#8221; and the newly formed empire will start as a subjuga=
ted
one instead. </p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Pirate <span
class=3DSpellE>Respawn</span> commands:</b> The <span class=3DGramE>command=
 <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><span class=3DSpellE><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>piraterespawn</i></span> will toggle t=
he
game setting allowing or forbidding the creation of new pirate empires duri=
ng
the game. You can also <span class=3DSpellE>used</span> the <span class=3DG=
ramE>command
<i style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>!</i></span><span class=3DSpellE><i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>respawnpiratesnow</i></span> to genera=
te new
pirates immediately if the current number of pirates is below the number
specified in the game setup.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Invasion Stra=
tegy:</b>
This is a little <span class=3DSpellE>subgame</span> you can play when inva=
ding a
planet to try and guess the opposing side&#8217;s strategy. If you are
successful your troops will receive a bonus. If not, they will be penalized.
Settings are controlled in the BaconSettings.txt file. Access with the <i
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>alt-ctrl-right click </i>menu on the t=
arget
planet with the planet selected. If you quit after taking a turn it counts =
as a
loss.</p>

